{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbe815195-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s8141"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"8141"},"text":"§ 8141.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Congressional findings","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The Congress finds and declares—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbe815196-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s8141/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" that artistic, cultural, and historic resources, including urban design, constitute an integral part of a suitable living environment for the residents of the Nation’s urban areas, and should be available to all residents of such areas, regardless of income;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbe815197-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s8141/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" that the development or preservation of such resources is a significant and necessary factor in restoring and maintaining the vitality of the urban environment, and can serve as a catalyst for improving decaying or deteriorated urban communities and expanding economic opportunities, and for creating a sense of community identity, spirit, and pride; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbe815198-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s8141/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" that the encouragement and support of local initiatives to develop or preserve such resources, particularly in connection with federally assisted housing or community development activities or in communities with a high proportion of low-income residents, is an appropriate function of the Federal Government.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbe815199-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/557/tVIII/s802"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–557, title VIII, § 802","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-10-31"},"text":"Oct. 31, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/2122"},"text":"92 Stat. 2122","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbe81519a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idbe81519b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitle","id":"idbe81519c-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For short title of this subchapter as the “Livable Cities Act of 1978”, see ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/557/s801"},"text":"section 801 of Pub. L. 95–557","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s8101"},"text":"section 8101 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
